    "problem_statement": "SPI mode 3 transfers report an incorrect idle SCK polarity.\n\nThis SPI flash controller exposes CPOL and CPHA through the CTRL register. In mode 3, firmware expects the controller to hold SCK high while the bus is idle and to return to that level after a transfer finishes. Instead, the current shifter keeps SCK fixed low while idle because CPOL is never propagated into the shifter path.\n\nRelevant behavior crosses several files: `src/rtl/spi_flash_regs.sv` decodes CPOL/CPHA from CTRL; `src/rtl/spi_flash_ctrl_top.sv` routes those settings into the shifter; `src/rtl/spi_flash_shifter.sv` generates SCK and sample timing.\n\nExpected fix: CPOL=1 should produce idle-high SCK whenever the controller is not actively shifting.",
