    "problem_statement": "Sticky IRQ and FIFO pending status do not stay latched across a read-clear sequence.\n\nWhen TX/RX FIFO overflow raises an interrupt, firmware expects the IRQ status and the FIFO-empty/pending status to remain visible even after the receive queue has been drained, until CONTROL[5] explicitly clears the interrupt path. The current IRQ block mirrors the live FIFO occupancy directly, so the pending view can collapse before software acknowledges it.\n\nRelevant behavior crosses several files: `src/rtl/spi_flash_fifo.sv` generates FIFO overflow and occupancy state; `src/rtl/spi_flash_irq.sv` owns sticky interrupt and latched FIFO status behavior; `src/rtl/spi_flash_regs.sv` exposes the status bits through the register map.\n\nExpected fix: the sticky IRQ and the exposed FIFO pending status should remain latched until the explicit clear operation is observed.",
